Add an alias to .bash_aliases in Linux or .profile in OpenBSD.
alias mps="/path/to/mps.sh"
be sure to reload .bash_aliases - source .bash_aliases

Examples:
mps album "back in black"
mps album "back in black" | mps add

mps ls | grep -i acdc
mps ls | grep -i acdc | mps add

mps save acdc
mps load acdc

mps artist metallica | grep -v "$(mps album 'master of puppets')" - list all metallica songs with the exception of those on the master of puppets album
